## Testing plan

Gates: `build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests` (all three).

- `build` gate: `dotnet build Berreman.slnx -c Release` MUST pass with `FitQuality.fs`, `Synthesis.fs`, the UI `SynthesisFitPage.fs` (public Avalonia.FuncUI NuGet, no clone), and `BerremanTests/OptimizationTests.fs` compiling.
- `unit-tests` gate: runs `BerremanTests` (`dotnet test --no-build -c Release` from `Berreman/BerremanTests/`); the new `OptimizationTests.fs` MUST pass over the full `DesignParameters`→`MeritFunction`→`optimize`→`AlglibAdapter`→`OpticalSystemSolver` path with the real solver (no stub) and MUST NOT depend on the UI project.
  - AC-G9: `LocalRefinement` + `LevenbergMarquardt` reproduces the expected converged parameters and final χ² within the stated tolerance (recorded-Wolfram fixture path a, OR self-consistency/regression path b per the applied re-scoping).
  - AC-G3 (bounded-fit): a thickness started outside its range terminates inside the G.3 bounds with no negative `Thickness`.
  - AC-G6 (needle-insertion): the films list grows by exactly one `Layer` and post-insertion merit ≤ pre-insertion.
  - AC-F3/AC-F7/AC-F5/AC-F8 cross-checks (Mueller equivalence, energy balance, ellipsometry round-trip, colorimetry sanity) per the line-1002 test description.
- `constructor-unit-tests` gate: runs `OpticalConstructor.Tests`; stays green (this slice's optimization additions are exercised end-to-end in `BerremanTests`, AC-G5/AC-G7/AC-G8 covered as below).
  - AC-G5: a `FitReport` exposes χ²/MSE, correlation matrix, confidence intervals, per-sample residuals, and is writable as a `.binz` sidecar (never inside canonical JSON).
  - AC-G7: clicking Cancel stops the G.5/G.9 loop cooperatively and the page can Revert to the pre-fit working `OpticalSystem`; Cancel is a distinct control from Start (tested at the model/`update` level, no Avalonia type — per P3).
  - AC-G8: on completion the result charts refresh through `plotComparison` showing fit-vs-measured overlay without a manual reload (model/`update`-level assertion).

## Risks

- **Medium/high.** The §G.11 / AC-G9 contract assumes recorded Wolfram ground-truth values that §G.0 places outside the repository; the applied re-scoping (fixture path a vs self-consistency path b) is the load-bearing decision — the worker MUST NOT fabricate numbers and present them as Wolfram ground truth, and MUST document the chosen path and the no-external-ground-truth limitation in the impl-log and state-of-the-world. The §G.8 covariance linear algebra MUST go through `MathNetNumericsMath.fs:5`, NOT ALGLIB (§A.8). The UI page MUST use the public MIT Avalonia.FuncUI NuGet, not the audit-gated clone, and the model/`update` MUST contain no Avalonia type so AC-G7/AC-G8 are testable headlessly (P3). §G.10 long-running execution defers to the Part J §J.10 job runner (slice 016) — this slice supplies only the progress payload and a single cancellable run; do not build a job-queue here. The needle/global loops MUST observe the cancellation flag (AC-G7).

## Hand-off

Part G is complete: [Standard] fit-quality reporting with the `FitReport` `.binz` sidecar (`FitQuality.fs`), [Standard] needle/tunnelling synthesis and global optimization (`Synthesis.fs`), the Synthesis/Fit operator page over the six-item UX checklist (`SynthesisFitPage.fs`, public Avalonia.FuncUI NuGet), and the Wolfram-reference validation in `BerremanTests/OptimizationTests.fs` over the real-solver full path. Slice 012 (Part H — charts) and later slices build on this. Under `Deferred`, record explicitly: (1) the chosen §G.11 / AC-G9 path (operator-supplied `.manual/` Wolfram fixture vs self-consistency/regression) and the no-external-Wolfram-ground-truth limitation; (2) the §G.10 long-running job runner is the Part J §J.10 harness (slice 016), to which this slice supplies only the per-iteration progress payload; (3) the still-open `NelderMead` simplex-backend decision from slice 009. Emit the state-of-the-world file with all required ATX headings (`Where we are`, `What's working`, `Tests`, `Architecture`, `Deferred`, `Gotchas`, `Changelog`) and a fenced `gates:` YAML baseline block carrying the updated `unit-tests` (BerremanTests) and `constructor-unit-tests` counts so the next slice's `count_at_least` gate has a baseline.
